LAMMPS data file: silica slab + binder fragment (Wave 5 reference fixture)
# Hand-curated reference for the Wave 5 layered cross-interaction regression.
# Tests that consume this file:
#   - tests/protocols/test_layered_combined_data.py
# What it captures:
#   * Si_tet pair coeff = INTERFACE FF Si (Heinz 2013, Emami 2014)
#   * O_br  pair coeff = INTERFACE FF O
#   * CA / HA pair coeff = GAFF2 aromatic
#   * 4 atom types ordered as Si_tet -> O_br -> CA -> HA
#
# IMPORTANT: this is NOT a runnable physical system. It exists only to
# lock the Pair Coeffs values and the LAYER_BULKFF protocol header. As a
# consequence:
#
#   * The silica slab IS electrically neutral (4 Si × +2.10 + 8 O × -1.05 = 0).
#   * The binder fragment is INTENTIONALLY NON-NEUTRAL: it is a 6-atom slice
#     of a toluene-style aromatic ring (4 CA × -0.115 + 2 HA × +0.115 = -0.230).
#     This is a *stub*, not a complete molecule, and the missing 2 HA atoms
#     would be needed to balance the ring. Wave 5 keeps the stub minimal so
#     the regression test can iterate quickly; the goal is the Pair Coeffs
#     lockdown, not a physically valid simulation cell.
#   * Total system charge = -0.230 (silica 0 + binder stub -0.230). The
#     regression test test_total_system_charge_is_well_defined asserts the
#     exact value so a future re-edit cannot silently change the stub.
#   * If a future PR expands the binder fragment to a complete neutral
#     molecule, BOTH this header AND the README AND the regression test
#     in tests/protocols/test_layered_combined_data.py must be updated
#     in the same commit.

